# GlobalLingua Academy

GlobalLingua Academy is a modular web platform designed to provide structured access to language learning services, academy information, and user interaction tools. The system is built to support users who want to explore language courses, stay informed about updates, and directly engage with the academy through consultations and communication channels.

The project follows a component-based frontend architecture with dynamic rendering, enabling scalability and maintainability without reliance on heavy frameworks.

---

## Overview

The platform focuses on delivering a centralized interface for:

* Language learning program discovery
* Academy information and structure
* News, updates, and promotional offers
* Consultation booking
* Direct communication with the academy

The system is designed around usability, modularity, and adaptability for future expansion into global markets.

---

## Core Features

### 1. Dynamic Component System

The application loads independent UI sections (header, hero, courses, pricing, testimonials, etc.) dynamically using asynchronous JavaScript. This allows:

* Separation of concerns
* Easier updates and maintenance
* Reusability of components

### 2. Course & Academy Presentation

Users can explore structured information about:

* Available language programs
* Teaching approach and methodology
* Academy positioning and value proposition

The platform reflects a typical modern language academy structure, including flexible scheduling and structured learning paths ([global-lingua.vercel.app][1]).

---

### 3. Interactive UI Modules

#### Video Section (YouTube Integration)

* Dynamic video switching system
* Playlist-style navigation
* Embedded YouTube player with autoplay

#### City / Inspiration Carousel

* Data-driven rendering system
* Horizontal navigation with responsive behavior
* Dataset abstraction for easy scaling

---

### 4. Multi-language System (i18n)

* Language switching via UI controls
* Persistent language selection using `localStorage`
* Attribute-based translation mapping (`data-i18n`)

---

### 5. Contact & Consultation System

* Form validation (client-side)
* User input handling
* Feedback messaging system

This module is designed as the base layer for future backend/API integration (e.g., CRM or booking systems).

---

### 6. Data-Driven Architecture

All dynamic sections (videos, cities, content blocks) are controlled via structured datasets.

Example:

* `cityDataset` → renders location carousels
* `videoDataset` → renders video modules

This separates logic from content and allows rapid scaling.

---

## Project Structure

```
/components
  header.html
  hero.html
  courses.html
  pricing.html
  inspiration.html
  testimonials.html
  contact.html
  footer.html
  youtubeShortsAI.html

/assets (images, media)

/scripts
  main.js (core logic)
```

---

## Technologies Used

* HTML5 (semantic structure)
* CSS3 (responsive layout, flex/grid)
* JavaScript (ES Modules, DOM manipulation)
* Fetch API (dynamic component loading)

The architecture intentionally avoids frameworks to maintain full control over rendering logic and performance.

---

## Architecture Concept

The project follows a consistent pattern:

```
DATA → RENDER → EVENT BINDING → STATE UPDATE
```

This pattern is applied across:

* Carousels
* Video modules
* Language system
* Form handling

---

## Use Case

The platform is intended for users who want to:

* Learn about a language academy
* Explore available courses and offers
* Stay updated with news and content
* Book consultations
* Contact the academy directly

---

## Future Development

Planned extensions include:

* Backend integration (Node.js / API layer)
* User authentication system
* Real-time chat assistant integration
* YouTube API automation
* Expansion into multilingual global markets
* Payment and booking system

---

## Installation & Usage

1. Clone the repository:

```
git clone https://github.com/Maks-Mm/GlobalLingua-.git
```

2. Open the project folder

3. Run using a local server (recommended):

```
npx serve
```

or open `index.html` directly in a browser.

